The paper deals with the problem of building learning agents that can navigate in constrained environments, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a method that combines supervised learning and reinforcement learning, which are both subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves training a deep convolutional network, which is a common technique in machine learning and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions testing the proposed method in a safety-constrained environment, which is related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper focuses on achieving good generalization, which is a common goal in machine learning (cs.LG).
